# form-data: transitive dependency via wiki-infobox-parser > request > form-data.
# No fix available upstream without breaking the wiki-infobox-parser feature.
# App only performs read-only GET requests; no multipart uploads occur,
# so the boundary-randomness and CRLF injection vectors are not exploitable here.
# Documented and accepted — see .snyk for matching Snyk-side justification.
CVE-2025-7783
CVE-2026-12143

# undici: bundled inside npm's own internal tooling (not our app's dependency).
# Path: usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/undici
# This is npm CLI's internal HTTP client used during package installs at
# build time, not code that runs in our application. No control over this
# via package.json; will resolve automatically as the official Node.js
# base image updates its bundled npm version.
CVE-2026-12151